text.section:
A person who violates any provision of the following subtitles or sections of this title is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction is subject to a fine not exceeding $1,000:
§ 12-311 ("Display of licenses");
Subtitle 4 ("Pharmacy permits");
§ 12-502(b) ("Pharmaceutical information");
§ 12-505 ("Labeling requirements for prescription medicines"); and
§ 12-604 ("General power to inspect drugs, devices, and other products").

A person who violates any provision of the following sections of this title is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction is subject to a fine not exceeding $1,000 or imprisonment not exceeding 1 year or both:
§ 12-602 ("Distribution permits");
§ 12-701 ("Practicing pharmacy without license");
§ 12-702 ("License obtained by false representation");
§ 12-703 ("Operating a pharmacy without permit");
§ 12-704 ("Misrepresentations"); and
§ 12-6B-12 ("Working as an unregistered pharmacy technician").
